Well, with the T4 engine,, you put the piston and cylinder onto the rod... 
after the piston is installed into the cylinder
it is quite easy.  I have a ring compressor like those.. but mine are home 
made with banding steel.... spot welded to the correct diameter, then 
hammered into a funnel like shape.. like the top of some race engine carbs.

